# Info
Invoked after all KubeJS plugins have finished initializing. This fires later than `[js]StartupEvents.init` and is a safer place to run startup logic that depends on plugins being loaded.

This event has no special fields - it simply signals that the post-initialization phase is complete.

# Example

```js
StartupEvents.postInit(event => {
	console.log('All KubeJS plugins have loaded!')
})
```
